The paper focuses on the evolution of deep neural networks, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of genetic encoding schemes and the optimization of network architectures are also key topics in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments conducted in the paper involve object categorization and object detection, which are tasks commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed method on parallel computing hardware architectures, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents results on the performance of different deep neural network architectures, which is a topic of interest in the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
